  <P>In this example, PROPFIND is invoked on the collection resource <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.foo.bar/container/">http://www.foo.bar/container/</A>,=
 with a=20
  propfind XML element containing the propname XML element, meaning the =
name of=20
  all properties should be returned. Since no Depth header is present, =
it=20
  assumes its default value of "infinity", meaning the name of the =
properties on=20
  the collection and all its progeny should be returned.=20
  <P>Consistent with the previous example, resource <BR><A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.foo.bar/container/">http://www.foo.bar/container/</A> =
has six=20
  properties defined on it, <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.foo.bar/boxschema/bigbox">http://www.foo.bar/boxschema=
/bigbox</A>,=20
