  <P>The resource <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.foo.bar/container/index.html">http://www.foo.bar/conta=
iner/index.html</A>,=20
  a member of the "container" collection, has nine properties defined on =
it, <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.foo.bar/boxschema/bigbox">http://www.foo.bar/boxschema=
/bigbox</A>,=20
  DAV:creationdate, <BR>DAV:displayname, DAV:getcontentlength,=20
  DAV:getcontenttype, DAV:getetag, DAV:getlastmodified, =
DAV:resourcetype, and=20
  <BR>DAV:supportedlock.=20
  <P>This example also demonstrates the use of XML namespace scoping, =
and the=20
  default namespace. Since the "xmlns" attribute does not contain an =
explicit=20
  "shorthand name" (prefix) letter, the namespace applies by default to =
all=20
  enclosed elements. Hence, all elements which do not explicitly state =
the=20
  namespace to which they belong are members of the "DAV:" namespace =
schema.=20
  <P></P>
