  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10>8.10</A> LOCK Method</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>The following sections describe the LOCK method, which is used to =
take out=20
  a lock of any access type. These sections on the LOCK method describe =
only=20
  those semantics that are specific to the LOCK method and are =
independent of=20
  the access type of the lock being requested.=20
  <P>Any resource which supports the LOCK method <STRONG>MUST</STRONG>, =
at=20
  minimum, support the XML request and response formats defined herein.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT>
  <HR>

  <DD>
  <DT><EM><A name=3Dpage-46>Page 46</A></EM>
  <DD>
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.1>8.10.1</A> Operation</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>A LOCK method invocation creates the lock specified by the lockinfo =
XML=20
  element on the Request-URI. Lock method requests =
<STRONG>SHOULD</STRONG> have=20
  a XML request body which contains an owner XML element for this lock =
request,=20
  unless this is a refresh request. The LOCK request may have a Timeout =
header.=20
  <P>Clients <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> assume that locks may arbitrarily =
disappear=20
  at any time, regardless of the value given in the Timeout header. The =
Timeout=20
  header only indicates the behavior of the server if "extraordinary"=20
  circumstances do not occur. For example, an administrator may remove a =
lock at=20
  any time or the system may crash in such a way that it loses the =
record of the=20
  lock's existence. The response <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> contain the value =
of the=20
  lockdiscovery property in a prop XML element.=20
  <P>In order to indicate the lock token associated with a newly created =
lock, a=20
  Lock-Token response header <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> be included in the =
response=20
  for every successful LOCK request for a new lock. Note that the =
Lock-Token=20
  header would not be returned in the response for a successful refresh =
LOCK=20
  request because a new lock was not created.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.2>8.10.2</A> The Effect of Locks on =
Properties=20
  and Collections</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>The scope of a lock is the entire state of the resource, including =
its body=20
  and associated properties. As a result, a lock on a resource=20
  <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> also lock the resource's properties.=20
  <P>For collections, a lock also affects the ability to add or remove =
members.=20
  The nature of the effect depends upon the type of access control =
involved.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.3>8.10.3</A> Locking Replicated=20
Resources</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>A resource may be made available through more than one URI. However =
locks=20
  apply to resources, not URIs. Therefore a LOCK request on a resource=20
  <STRONG>MUST NOT</STRONG> succeed if can not be honored by all the =
URIs=20
  through which the resource is addressable.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.4>8.10.4</A> Depth and Locking</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>The Depth header may be used with the LOCK method. Values other =
than 0 or=20
  infinity <STRONG>MUST NOT</STRONG> be used with the Depth header on a =
LOCK=20
  method. All resources that support the LOCK method =
<STRONG>MUST</STRONG>=20
  support the Depth header.=20
  <P>A Depth header of value 0 means to just lock the resource specified =
by the=20
  Request-URI.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT>
  <HR>

  <DD>
  <DT><EM><A name=3Dpage-47>Page 47</A></EM>
  <DD>
  <P>If the Depth header is set to infinity then the resource specified =
in the=20
  Request-URI along with all its internal members, all the way down the=20
  hierarchy, are to be locked. A successful result <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> =
return=20
  a single lock token which represents all the resources that have been =
locked.=20
  If an UNLOCK is successfully executed on this token, all associated =
resources=20
  are unlocked. If the lock cannot be granted to all resources, a 409 =
(Conflict)=20
  status code <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> be returned with a response entity =
body=20
  containing a multistatus XML element describing which resource(s) =
prevented=20
  the lock from being granted. Hence, partial success is not an option. =
Either=20
  the entire hierarchy is locked or no resources are locked.=20
  <P>If no Depth header is submitted on a LOCK request then the request=20
  <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> act as if a "Depth:infinity" had been submitted. =

  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.5>8.10.5</A> Interaction with other=20
  Methods</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>The interaction of a LOCK with various methods is dependent upon =
the lock=20
  type. However, independent of lock type, a successful DELETE of a =
resource=20
  <STRONG>MUST</STRONG> cause all of its locks to be removed.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.6>8.10.6</A> Lock Compatibility =
Table</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>The table below describes the behavior that occurs when a lock =
request is=20
  made on a resource.=20
  <P><PRE>   Current lock state/  |   Shared Lock   |   Exclusive
   Lock request         |                 |   Lock
   =
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D+=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D+=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=3D=
=3D=3D=3D=3D
   None                 |   True          |   True
   ---------------------+-----------------+--------------
   Shared Lock          |   True          |   False
   ---------------------+-----------------+--------------
   Exclusive Lock       |   False         |   False*
   ------------------------------------------------------
</PRE>
  <P>Legend: True =3D lock may be granted. False =3D lock <STRONG>MUST =
NOT</STRONG>=20
  be granted. *=3DIt is illegal for a principal to request the same lock =
twice.=20
  <P>The current lock state of a resource is given in the leftmost =
column, and=20
  lock requests are listed in the first row. The intersection of a row =
and=20
  column gives the result of a lock request. For example, if a shared =
lock is=20
  held on a resource, and an exclusive lock is requested, the table =
entry is=20
  "false", indicating the lock must not be granted.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT>
  <HR>

  <DD>
  <DT><EM><A name=3Dpage-48>Page 48</A></EM>
  <DD>
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.7>8.10.7</A> Status Codes</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>200 (OK) - The lock request succeeded and the value of the =
lockdiscovery=20
  property is included in the body.=20
  <P>412 (Precondition Failed) - The included lock token was not =
enforceable on=20
  this resource or the server could not satisfy the request in the =
lockinfo XML=20
  element.=20
  <P>423 (Locked) - The resource is locked, so the method has been =
rejected.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.8>8.10.8</A> Example - Simple Lock=20
  Request</STRONG>
  <DD>
  <P>&gt;&gt;Request=20
  <P>LOCK /workspace/webdav/proposal.doc HTTP/1.1 <BR>Host: =
webdav.sb.aol.com=20
  <BR>Timeout: Infinite, Second-4100000000 <BR>Content-Type: text/xml;=20
  charset=3D"utf-8" <BR>Content-Length: xxxx <BR>Authorization: Digest=20
  username=3D"ejw", <BR>realm=3D"ejw@webdav.sb.aol.com", nonce=3D"...",=20
  <BR>uri=3D"/workspace/webdav/proposal.doc", <BR>response=3D"...", =
opaque=3D"..."=20
  <P><PRE>   &lt;?xml version=3D"1.0" encoding=3D"utf-8" ?&gt;
   &lt;D:lockinfo xmlns:D=3D'DAV:'&gt;
     &lt;D:lockscope&gt;&lt;D:exclusive/&gt;&lt;/D:lockscope&gt;
     &lt;D:locktype&gt;&lt;D:write/&gt;&lt;/D:locktype&gt;
     &lt;D:owner&gt;
          &lt;D:href&gt;<A =
href=3D"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~ejw/contact.html</D:href">http://www.ics.=
uci.edu/~ejw/contact.html</D:HREF< a>&gt;
     &lt;/D:owner&gt;
   &lt;/D:lockinfo&gt;
</PRE>
  <P>&gt;&gt;Response=20
  <P>HTTP/1.1 200 OK <BR>Content-Type: text/xml; charset=3D"utf-8"=20
  <BR>Content-Length: xxxx=20
  <P><PRE>   &lt;?xml version=3D"1.0" encoding=3D"utf-8" ?&gt;
   &lt;D:prop xmlns:D=3D"DAV:"&gt;
     &lt;D:lockdiscovery&gt;
          &lt;D:activelock&gt;
               &lt;D:locktype&gt;&lt;D:write/&gt;&lt;/D:locktype&gt;
               =
&lt;D:lockscope&gt;&lt;D:exclusive/&gt;&lt;/D:lockscope&gt;
               &lt;D:depth&gt;Infinity&lt;/D:depth&gt;
</PRE>
  <P></P>
  <DT>
  <HR>

  <DD>
  <DT><EM><A name=3Dpage-49>Page 49</A></EM>
  <DD>
  <P><PRE>               &lt;D:owner&gt;
                    &lt;D:href&gt;
                         <A =
href=3D"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~ejw/contact.html">http://www.ics.uci.edu/=
~ejw/contact.html</A>
                    &lt;/D:href&gt;
               &lt;/D:owner&gt;
               &lt;D:timeout&gt;Second-604800&lt;/D:timeout&gt;
               &lt;D:locktoken&gt;
                    &lt;D:href&gt;
               opaquelocktoken:e71d4fae-5dec-22d6-fea5-00a0c91e6be4
                    &lt;/D:href&gt;
               &lt;/D:locktoken&gt;
          &lt;/D:activelock&gt;
     &lt;/D:lockdiscovery&gt;
   &lt;/D:prop&gt;
</PRE>
  <P>This example shows the successful creation of an exclusive write =
lock on=20
  resource <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://webdav.sb.aol.com/workspace/webdav/proposal.doc">http://we=
bdav.sb.aol.com/workspace/webdav/proposal.doc</A>.=20
  The resource <A=20
  =
href=3D"http://www.ics.uci.edu/~ejw/contact.html">http://www.ics.uci.edu/=
~ejw/contact.html</A>=20
  contains contact information for the owner of the lock. The server has =
an=20
  activity-based timeout policy in place on this resource, which causes =
the lock=20
  to automatically be removed after 1 week (604800 seconds). Note that =
the=20
  nonce, response, and opaque fields have not been calculated in the=20
  Authorization request header.=20
  <P></P>
  <DT><STRONG><A name=3Dsec-8.10.9>8.10.9</A> Example - Refreshing a =
